{{Image Banner|image=022extra.jpg|caption=''New & Improved.''}}
{{Class 1e}}
'''Level 0.22''' is a sub-level designated between [[Level 0]] and [[Level 1]].

<div style="font-family:Amatic SC; background: #FF7700; color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid #000000; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #000000; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="5">Description</font></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Level_0.22.png|hovertext=Manmade.|caption=An image of Level 0.22.}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level_0.22-2.png|hovertext=Don't touch anything.|caption=Another image of Level 0.22, depicting brown walls.}}
'''Level 0.22''', commonly referred to as "Fully Remodeled," is an empty industrial building. It consists of fluorescent lights, a basic white ceiling, yellowish-green walls, and patterned gray carpets, with the typical appearance of light metal heaters, vents, and modernized office doors.<ref>This appearance isn't consistent and can vary from person to person, multiple wanderers reported the walls being a dark brown, while a single wanderer reported saying that the level vaguely looked like a modern kitchen. All wanderers showed photo evidence.</ref> The architecture of the level is an odd fusion of [[Level 0]] and seemingly man-made methods; the walls are indented for easier access to wiring, the paint color of walls tapers off into another color as if done in a haphazard fashion, and overall the space looks as though it was meant to serve an obscure purpose. Although the construction efforts in the level are poor, environmental and electrical hazards are a rare occurrence.

The level also possesses the same non-Euclidean nature from [[Level 0]]. To add onto this, the level is diverse in size, wanderers have reported '''Level 0.22''' being as small as a single room, while others reported to be exponentially large. It is currently unknown if '''Level 0.22''' generates completely differently for each person, or if the level is segmented into separate regions that do not connect to each other.

Despite the lack of any furniture, '''Level 0.22''' can feature modern-day construction equipment, such as hammers, paint buckets, or even forklifts. The objects seem to have appeared to be "used" in some way. The objects in question show signs of rust and breakage, which has led some to speculate that a group or person somehow "created" '''Level 0.22''' in some way. Despite the aforementioned weathering of the construction equipment, it is still in fairly decent condition and able to be salvaged and brought out of the sub-level for actual construction by wanderers.

<div style="font-family:Amatic SC; background: #FF7700; color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid #000000; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #000000; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="5">Addendum</font></div>
===Actualities===
{{Blurimage|file=Level_0.22-3.png|hovertext=Under Construction.|caption=An unconfirmed image of Level 0.22, depicting a kitchen inside the level.}}
'''Level 0.22''' is completely devoid of life, and has an [[Phenomenon_15|isolation effect]] similar to [[Level 0]] and [[Level 27]]. Because of this, nobody has ever encountered an entity, or another person. Attempts to create outposts and colonies have failed due to the reasons stated above,<ref>Many wanderers have reported [[Kats]] being in this Level, but due to the isolation effect, it's most likely false. In addition, all reports of entities being inside of '''Level 0.22''' are to be deemed fake.</ref> though it is still used to collect useful equipment.
===Occasional Hazards===
*Heaters spontaneously combusting.
*Loose ceiling lights.
*Rooms becoming extremely hot or cold.<ref>Varys from 44.444°C to 0°C (112°F to 32°F).</ref>
More frequently, shoddy craftsmanship has led to phenomena that are not dangerous but somewhat inconvenient, such as:

*Doors not being able to open.
*Dark rooms with lights that won't turn on.
*Malfunctioning electrical sockets.

