<div style="font-family:VCR OSD Mono;">I always thought that [[Level 0]] was not the best place to be in, you can't see anyone, there are no entities, and the ways to exit the level are very obscure. Hell, a group even tried to remodel the level for that same reason, but due to their unfamiliarity with an undocumented phenomenon in The Main Nine, the attempt was unsuccessful. However, knowing that there are now ways to work around the complication, making a successful revamp isn't the worst idea out there.. right?. Besides, many have done similar projects without help from others, so it shouldn't be impossible. So with that in mind, I began to gather supplies and begin the remodeling project.
[[File:NeverAgainRemastered.png|400x400px|center]]
=<center><big>'''?'''</big></center>=

===The Project===
I decided that this would be a "landmark" of some sorts, a place where wanderers can meet up and relax. At first, I didn't really have the supplies to begin the project — besides a couple of [[Architect Industries|supplies]] I stole off an [[Architect Industries]] employee; so I went off to [[Level 20]] to gather materials. I forgot how much I took from there; but I believed it was more than enough. It was a lot less efficient without a team working with me, but I was able to manage. I don't even remember how big that place was, but that doesn't matter. All I needed to figure out is to somehow stop the isolation effect in [[Level 0]] without the necessary equipment. As a result, I decided to rest and go on the trip back to [[Level 20|that warehouse]] for a while to get the materials need to create a makeshift version of the equipment, but when I eventually did get back.. Everything that I made was just.. '''Gone.''' And in its spot, only an ordinary section of [[Level 0]], with a door labeled "Renovations In Progress". As I opened the doorway, I saw it.

There it was, my unfinished creation, now completely taken form.

It wasn't long before I came to realize that I ran out of the stolen [[Architect Industries]] tech in my possession; thus, i had to pause further renovations.

Despite my work remaining unfinished, it was; for the most part, a success.
</div>


